{"title_page": "Us & Them", "text_new": "{{About|American television series||Us and Them (disambiguation){{!}}Us and Them}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name            = Us & Them\n| image                = \n| caption              = \n| show_name_2          = \n| genre                = Comedy\n| creator              = \n| based_on             = {{based on|''[[Gavin & Stacey]]''|[[James Corden]] and [[Ruth Jones (actress)|Ruth Jones]]}}\n| developer            = David J. Rosen\n| writer               = \n| director             = \n| creative_director    = \n| presenter            = \n| starring             = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Jason Ritter]]\n* [[Alexis Bledel]]\n* [[Dustin Ybarra]]\n* [[Ashlie Atkinson]]\n* [[Jane Kaczmarek]]\n* [[Kurt Fuller]]\n* [[Kerri Kenney-Silver]]\n* [[Michael Ian Black]]}}\n| judges               = \n| voices               = \n| narrated             = \n| theme_music_composer = \n| opentheme            = \n| endtheme             = \n| composer             = \n| country              = United States\n| language             = English\n| num_seasons          = 1\n| num_episodes         = 7\n| list_episodes        = #Episodes\n| executive_producer   = {{Plainlist|\n* David Rosen\n* [[Steve Coogan]]\n* [[Jane Tranter]]\n* [[Julie Gardner]]\n* James Corden\n* Ruth Jones\n* [[Henry Normal]]}}\n| producer             = \n| editor               = \n| location             = \n| cinematography       = \n| camera               = [[Single-camera setup|Single-camera]]\n| runtime              = \n| company              = {{Plainlist|\n* Men of Science\n* BBC Worldwide Productions\n* [[Sony Pictures Television]]}}\n| distributor          = Sony Pictures Television\n| channel              = [[Fox Broadcasting Company|Fox]] (unaired)<br>[[Sony Crackle]] (2018)\n| picture_format       = \n| audio_format         =\n| first_run            = \n| first_aired          = {{Start date|2018|10|1}}\n| last_aired           = \n| preceded_by          = \n| followed_by          = \n| related              = \n| website              = \n| website_title        = Official website\n| production_website   = \n}}\n\n'''''Us & Them''''' is an American television series based on the British series ''[[Gavin & Stacey]]'' created by [[James Corden]] and [[Ruth Jones (actress)|Ruth Jones]]. It was adapted for an American audience by David J. Rosen. The series was scheduled to premiere on [[Fox Broadcasting Company|Fox]] as a mid-season replacement in the [[2013\u201314 United States network television schedule|2013\u201314 season]]; however, Fox did not air the series. Instead, streaming service [[Sony Crackle]] streamed all seven episodes on October 1, 2018.\n\n==Premise==\nAfter a six-month-long online romance, Gavin, who lives in New York, and Stacey, who lives in Pennsylvania, decide to meet in person.  Their crazy families and friends constantly interfere in their budding relationship, which becomes more of a challenge than living in different states.\n\n==Cast==\n* [[Jason Ritter]] as Gavin<ref name=\"cast\">{{cite news|last=Andreeva|first=Nellie|title=Aasif Mandvi & Michael Ian Black Join New Fox Series \u2018Us & Them\u2019|url=http://www.deadline.com/2013/08/aasif-mandvi-michael-ian-black-join-new-fox-series-us-them/|accessdate=August 24, 2013|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=August 23, 2013}}</ref>\n* [[Alexis Bledel]] as Stacey<ref name=\"cast\"/>\n* [[Dustin Ybarra]] as Archie, Gavin's best friend\n* [[Ashlie Atkinson]] as Nessa, Stacey's best friend<ref name=\"cast\"/>\n* [[Michael Ian Black]] as Brian, Stacey's uncle<ref name=\"cast\"/>\n* [[Jane Kaczmarek]] as Pam, Gavin's mother\n* [[Kurt Fuller]] as Michael, Gavin's father\n* [[Kerri Kenney-Silver]] as Gwen, Stacey's mother\n* [[Aasif Mandvi]] as Dave Coaches, Nessa's ex and a security guard for the [[Dave Matthews Band]]<ref name=\"cast\"/>\n\n==Production and release==\nThe series was scheduled to premiere on [[Fox Broadcasting Company|Fox]] as a mid-season replacement in the [[2013\u201314 United States network television schedule|2013\u201314 season]].<ref name=\"premiere\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/news/2013/05/13/fox-announces-primetime-slate-for-2013-2014-season-254005/20130513fox01/|title=FOX Announces Primetime Slate for 2013-2014 Season|date=May 13, 2013|work=The Futon Critic|accessdate=August 24, 2013}}</ref> On May 8, 2013, Fox placed a thirteen-episode order for the [[Single-camera setup|single-camera]] comedy.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/fox-comedy-series-orders-chris-519678|title=Fox Comedy Series Orders: Chris Meloni Entry, 'Brooklyn Nine-Nine,' 'Enlisted,' 'Us & Them'|date=May 8, 2013|last=Rose|first=Lacey|last2=Goldberg|first2=Lesley|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|accessdate=May 12, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.tvguide.com/News/Fox-Fall-2013-Comedy-Brooklyn-Enlisted-Jack-1065183.aspx|title=Fox Orders Brooklyn Nine-Nine, Enlisted, Us & Them and Surviving Jack|date=May 8, 2013|last=Abrams|first=Natalie|work=[[TV Guide]]|accessdate=May 12, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.deadline.com/2013/05/fox-picks-up-andy-samberg-chris-meloni-comedies-us-them-and-enlisted-almost-doubles-new-series-volume/|title=Fox Picks Up Andy Samberg & Chris Meloni Comedies, 'Us & Them' And 'Enlisted', Almost Doubles New Series Volume|date=May 8, 2013|last=Andreeva|first=Nellie|work=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|accessdate=May 12, 2013}}</ref> On October 11, 2013, it was revealed that Fox had cut back the episode order to seven episodes.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.deadline.com/2013/10/fox-cuts-back-order-for-us-them/ | title=Fox Cuts Back Order For ''Us & Them'' | website=Deadline Hollywood | date=October 11, 2013 | accessdate=December 22, 2013 | author=Andreeva, Nellie}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/showatch/us-and-them/ | title=Showatch for ''Us & Them'' | publisher=The Futon Critic | accessdate=December 22, 2013}}</ref> In 2014, Vulture revealed that Fox would not air the series.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Adalian|first1=Josef|title=Fox Won't Even Burn Off Episodes of Us & Them|url=http://www.vulture.com/2014/06/fox-wont-even-burn-off-episodes-of-us-them.html|website=Vulture|accessdate=June 10, 2014}}</ref> The series was first broadcast in South Africa on [[M-Net]].<ref>{{cite web|title=New In September|url=http://mnet.dstv.com/2014/08/07/coming-soon-in-september/|accessdate=September 5, 2014}}</ref>  All seven episodes were available on Korean major IPTV networks. However, in September 2018, streaming service [[Sony Crackle]] announced it would be streaming all seven episodes starting October 1, finally giving the show its American release.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.tvobscurities.com/2018/09/sony-crackle-stream-unaired-fox-sitcom-us-them-beginning-october-1st/|title=Sony Crackle to Stream Unaired FOX Sitcom Us & Them Beginning October 1st|website=TVObscurities|first=Robert|last=Jay|date=September 16, 2018|accessdate=September 30, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Episodes==\n{{Episode table |background=#87D1F8 |overall= |title= |titleR=<ref name=loc>{{citation|url=http://cocatalog.loc.gov/|title=United States Copyright Office|publisher=Sony Pictures}}</ref> |director= |writer= |airdate=y |released=y |prodcode= |episodes=\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 1\n| Title           = Pilot\n| DirectedBy      = [[Michael Patrick Jann]]\n| WrittenBy       = David J. Rosen\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2018|10|1}}\n| ProdCode        = 100\n| ShortSummary    = A young couple trying to take their relationship to the next level must overcome their geographical differences as well as their eccentric group of friends and family.\n| LineColor       = 87D1F8\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 2\n| Title           = Crunch & Brunch\n| DirectedBy      = Michael Patrick Jann\n| WrittenBy       = David J. Rosen\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2018|10|1}}\n| ProdCode        = 101\n| ShortSummary    = After Stacey causes an 