3819}}\n* Zinsmeister, Karl. ''Boots on the Ground: A Month with the 82nd Airborne in the Battle for Iraq''. New York: Truman Talley Books/St. Martin's Press, 2003. {{ISBN|0-312-32663-7}} {{OCLC|52775207}}\n* Zinsmeister, Karl, Dan Jurgens, and Raul Trevino. ''Combat Zone: True Tales of GIs in Iraq''. New York, NY: Marvel Comics, 2005. {{ISBN|0-7851-1516-1}} {{OCLC|61373604}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons|82nd Airborne Division}}\n* [http://www.bragg.army.mil/ Fort Bragg Homepage]\n* [http://www.dday-overlord.com/eng/82nd_airborne_division.htm Historical Account of the 82nd Airborne Division]\n* [http://www.lonesentry.com/gi_stories_booklets/82ndairborne/ All American: The Story of the 82nd Airborne Division] \u2013 World War II unit history booklet, 1945\n* [http://www.combatreels.com/82nd_Airborne_Division_Normandy_DVD.cfm 82nd Airborne Combat Footage DVD World War II Normandy June 1944 ]\n* [http://www.combatreels.com/82nd_Airborne_Division_Europe_DVD.cfm 82nd AB Combat Footage DVD World War II including Operation Market Garden September 1944]\n* [http://www.scls.lib.wi.us/mcmillan/history/82nd/82_18.pdf The 82nd Airborne Division]\n* [http://www.ushmm.org/wlc/en/article.php?ModuleId=10006159 THE 82ND AIRBORNE DIVISION]\n* [http://www.ww2-airborne.us/division/82_overview.html The 82nd Airborne during World War II]\n* [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ojlKy5Lib4g 82nd Airborne Division, NYC Victory Parade, 12 Jan 1946]\n* {{Internet Archive short film|id=gov.archives.arc.2569606|name=Big Picture: Arctic Night}}\n* {{Internet Archive short film|id=gov.archives.arc.2569486|name=Big Picture: All American}}\n* {{Internet Archive short film|id=gov.archives.arc.2569780|name=Big Picture: This is Our Strength}}\n* {{Internet Archive short film|id=gov.dod.dimoc.26966|name=STAFF FILM REPORT 66-17A (1966)}}\n* {{Internet Archive short film|id=gov.dod.dimoc.26967|name=STAFF FILM REPORT 66-18A (1966)}}\n* {{Internet Archive short film|id=gov.dod.dimoc.26968|name=STAFF FILM R